From: PS3 Custom Toolchain <noreply@example.invalid>
Subject: [PATCH] rsx/gcm_sys.h: union-alias gcmSurface.antiAlias / .antialias

PSL1GHT's gcmSurface struct names the AA field `antiAlias` (camel);
Sony samples write it as `antialias` (lower).  Same byte at the same
offset, same values, same struct layout.

Anonymous union lets both spellings resolve against the same storage
so sample code written against either convention compiles unchanged
against the shared struct.  Zero runtime cost — the compiler picks
a single field to emit; no runtime chooser.

Covers the gap uncovered while bringing Sony
`samples/sdk/graphics/gcm/basic/main.cpp` through our SDK build.

Signed-off-by: PS3 Custom Toolchain <noreply@example.invalid>
---
 ppu/include/rsx/gcm_sys.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/ppu/include/rsx/gcm_sys.h b/ppu/include/rsx/gcm_sys.h
--- a/ppu/include/rsx/gcm_sys.h
+++ b/ppu/include/rsx/gcm_sys.h
@@ -774,7 +774,7 @@ typedef struct _gcmSurface
 	- \ref GCM_SURFACE_SQUARE_CENTERED_4
 	- \ref GCM_SURFACE_SQUARE_ROTATED_4
 	*/
-	u8 antiAlias;
+	union { u8 antiAlias; u8 antialias; };

 	/*! \brief Format of the color buffer.

